original: Johanson, Bertil Viktor, civilingenjör, Göteborg, f. 5/5/93 i Skön, Väs-ternorrl. 1., av dir. G. J. o. Lydia Eng-wall. — Stud:ex. v. Lundsbergs sk. 12, KTH (M) 12-16. Anst. v. SKF i G^bg o. Sthlm 16-21, v. Kjellberg & Son’s Ltd ’samt Kjellberg’s Successor Ltd i Tokyo 21-32, chef f. SKF Industries of Japan i Tokyo 32, num. v. SKF i Gbg. Led. av Sv. tekn:-fören.
translated: Johanson, Bertil Viktor, engineer, Gothenburg, b. 5/5/93 in Skön, Västernorrland County, son of director G. J. and Lydia Engwall. — Graduated from Lundsbergs sk. 12, KTH (M) 12-16. Employed by SKF in Gothenburg and Stockholm 16-21, employed by Kjellberg & Son's Ltd and Kjellberg's Successor Ltd in Tokyo 21-32, became CEO of SKF Industries of Japan in Tokyo in 32, currently affiliated with SKF in Gothenburg. Member of the Swedish Association of Engineers. Married in an unspecified year.
